xADL - architecture description language
     - used to describe various aspects of architecture of a software system

common arch constructs:
1 configurations - topological arrangement of components & connectors
2 components - loci of computation
3 connectors - loci of communication
(loci meaning - a particular position or place where something occurs or is situated)

xADL is an XML based language.
What to draw?
1 formal description language (FDL)
  - purpose, architecture, functionality, data management and security. User experience
2 box and line diagram
3 any uml diagram (preferably use case becuase its easy)

